  <title>Teacher Note: Turtle Geometry</title>
  <!-- <image source="turtles/Figures/apple.jpg" width="50px%" alt="teacher note"/> -->
  <p>The turtle is actually useful for exploring a wide variety of ideas in geometry.  The book <url href="http://www.amazon.com/Turtle-Geometry-Mathematics-Artificial-Intelligence/dp/0262510375" visual="http://www.amazon.com/Turtle-Geometry-Mathematics-Artificial-Intelligence/dp/0262510375">Turtle Geometry</url> does a wonderful job of showing how turtles can be used to explore a wide variety of geometric, mathematical, and scientific ideas (e.g., using turtles to model insect behavior).  The example <term>pattern</term> below is drawn from that book.</p>
